1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 Bc5 7. O-O O-O 8.
Nxd5 Qxd5 9. Ng5 $5 {As it happens quite often Levon comes up with an
interesting opening idea.} Qd8 {Clearly the best square for the queen.} 10.
Nxh7 ({Pointless would have been} 10. Qc2 Qxg5 ({There is nothing wrong with} 
10... Bxf2+ 11. Rxf2 Qxg5 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Qxc6 Be6) 11. Qxc5 {this occurred
in Erban, S-Reitinger, J Svetla nad Sazavou 1997 Black had to play} Nd4 $1 $146 {
here} 12. f4 ({Black is better after} 12. e3 Ne2+ 13. Kh1 Qh5 $1 14. Qxc7 Bg4
$36 {with a strong initiative on the light squares. If white captures on b7,
Black might continue with Rae8 and e4! Meanwhile, f2-f3 is not recommended due
to Nxg3 check.}) 12... Qh5 13. Qxe5 Nxe2+ 14. Kf2 Qxe5 15. fxe5 Nd4 {Black
most probably has some pull considering his powerful centralized knight,
although white should be able to equalize with precise play.}) 10... Re8 ({
Of course not} 10... Kxh7 $2 11. Qc2+ $16 {and White regains the piece with
dividends.}) 11. Ng5 ({Obviously} 11. h4 $2 f6 $17 {is not an option for White.
}) 11... Qxg5 12. Bxc6 ({The alternative is} 12. d4 {here the play might
continue} Qh5 13. dxc5 Rd8 14. Bd2 Nd4 15. f3 ({or} 15. Re1 Bf5) 15... e4 $44 {
Black has full compensation for the sacrificed pawn due to enormous central
activity.}) 12... bxc6 13. d4 Qh5 $1 {Black should play actively.} ({The
passive} 13... Qe7 14. dxc5 Bh3 15. Re1 Qxc5 16. Be3 Qd5 17. f3 $14 {is
slightly better for White. Black has to defend an unpleasant position without
chances to win.}) 14. dxc5 e4 15. h4 Qg4 ({I would rather choose} 15... Bg4 16.
Re1 Rad8 17. Qc2 f6 {followed by 18...g5 with very an interesting initiative
for Black.}) 16. Bf4 {this position occurred in Aronian,L (2799)-Caruana,F 
(2807) Saint Louis 2017 Black should haveplayed} Ba6 $1 $146 17. Re1 e3 $1 {
with sufficient counterplay. It is well known that positions with
opposite-colored bishops favor the attacking side and here black is the one
with initiative. White's material advantage is purely symbolic as his weak
king will need constant attention.} *

